RUN: @mhost_bin -s 8.8.8.8 --no-system-lookups --ascii --no-color check example.com -i -p --no-ns --no-caa --no-ttl

CHECK: > Options: mode=multi, concurrent nameservers=10, max. nameservers=100, concurrent requests=5, retries=0, timeout=5s, ndots=1, abort on error, abort on timeout
CHECK-NEXT: > Running DNS lookups for all available records.
CHECK-NEXT: - Sending [[\d+]] requests to [[\d+]] nameserver[[s*]] for [[\d+]] record types of 1 name.
CHECK-NEXT: - Received
CHECK-NEXT: * SOA:
CHECK-NEXT: * NS:
CHECK-NEXT: * NS:
CHECK-NEXT: * MX:
CHECK-NEXT: * TXT:
CHECK: * TXT:
CHECK: * A:
CHECK: * AAAA:
CHECK: > Checking SOA lints
CHECK-NEXT: * Authoritative SOA records
CHECK: - Received
CHECK: * Comparing authoritative with looked up SOA records
CHECK-NEXT: = All authoritative SOA records are in sync
CHECK-NEXT: = Looked up SOA records match authoritative SOA records
CHECK-NEXT: > Checking CNAME lints
CHECK-NEXT: * Apex
CHECK-NEXT: * MX
CHECK: * SRV
CHECK: * CNAME
CHECK: = Apex zone without CNAME
CHECK-NEXT: = MX do not point to CNAME
CHECK-NEXT: = SRV do not point to CNAME
CHECK-NEXT: = CNAME do not point to CNAME
CHECK-NEXT: > Checking MX hygiene lints
CHECK: = Domain has a valid Null MX record
CHECK: > Checking SPF TXT records lints
CHECK-NEXT: = Found exactly one SPF record
CHECK-NEXT: = Successfully parsed SPF record
CHECK-NEXT: > Checking DMARC TXT records lints
CHECK: - Received
CHECK: = Found exactly one DMARC record
CHECK-NEXT: = Successfully parsed DMARC record
CHECK: > Checking DNSSEC lints
CHECK: > Checking HTTPS/SVCB record lints
CHECK: + Finished.
CHECK-NEXT: = No issues found.
